Rating: 3
I think this recipe worked well. The trick is getting the onions to carmelize - which takes time. Other reviews suggested using more beef broth to get the deep color. I used a variety of pans to carmelize and found that using a non-stick pan does not work well. It prevents being able to deglaze the pan, which gives the color and flavor. Of the 3 pans I used, the cast iron skillet was best, providing beautiful color and carmelizing in under 45 minutes. I added the garlic well into the cooking process - so it wasn't too mild. I used 1/2 butter and 1/2 olive oil in recommended quantities. This was delicious - I seldom give 4 forks.

