Rating: 4
Very good. I took others advice from this and other reviews, and I baked the onion and garlic, whole, at 375 for an hour, then peeled and sliced. gave the onion a wonderful sweet flavor. made a double batch, and even after baking the onion, I carmelized for an hour, and this wasnt enough. patience is the name of the game here, take your time carmelizing the onions, and keep the heat low, or risk burning (which I did). I didnt add the mustard, and I dont think you will need it. I would also add more beef broth, I like my onion soup with more broth and less onion, this worked out, as I ended up adding more, which made more soup. Also used a good red wine (merlot), which gave the soup a nice kick.

