Best french onion soup ever! Made the recipe with the 2:1 beef to chicken stock ratio suggested by others, used a heaping tablespoon of mustard, gruyere cheese, red wine, and used two bay leaves. I suggest letting the bread soak in the soup and then putting the soup under the broiler toasting it then putting the cheese on top and toasting again. It gives the surface a crisp consistency letting your spoon crack through the surface without pushing the toast to the bottom of the cup. Even though the Gruyere cheese is expensive use it, it makes the difference.

