Rating: 3
This is a very good soup although I agree that red wine is better. Save time by cooking the onions in a crockpot. Slice, add 1/2 cup butter and cook on low for 12 to 14 hours. It is almost impossible to overcook them and the juice left in the pot makes a delicious addition to the soup. Refridgerate the juice and take off the onion flavored butter before using. The butter is wonderful for sautes and stir fries.

